de.boereck.matcher.helpers

Class MatchHelpers

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.boereck.matcher.helpers.MatchHelpers

  • public final class MatchHelpers
extends Object
    This class provides static methods and fields that help with defining matches with CaseMatchers.

    This class is not intended to be instantiated or sub-classed.

      • _try

        public static <T> AdvPredicate<T> _try(Predicate<T> toTry)
                                throws NullPointerException
        Exception in wrapped Predicate is mapped to "false", on regular execution, the result of the wrapped Predicate will be forwarded. This method can be used to navigate object graphs without having to worry about null references. Be aware that Exceptions do cost a lot of runtime!
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of object to be checked
        Parameters:
        toTry - predicate being executed, which may throw an exception
        Returns:
        predicate that will return false if the wrapping predicate throws an exception during evaluation. If the evaluation does not throw, the result of the wrapped predicate will be returned.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if toTry is null.

      • tryMap

        public static <I,O> OptionalMapper<I,O> tryMap(Function<I,O> function)
                                        throws NullPointerException
        Returns a mapper that will try to perform the given function, if an exception is thrown during the execution, the mapper will swallow the exception and return an empty Optional instead. The caller of this function cannot distinguish between a null result returned by the wrapped function or if an exception was caught. In both cases an empty optional is returned.
        Type Parameters:
        I - Type of input of function
        O - Type of output of function
        Parameters:
        function - mapping function that is tried to executed.
        Returns:
        function that will try to perform the given function, if an exception is thrown during the execution, the mapper will swallow the exception and return an empty Optional instead.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if function is null

      • nullAware

        public static <I,O> OptionalMapper<I,O> nullAware(Function<I,O> f)
        The returned function will return an empty Optional if the input object is null. Otherwise the function f will be called and the returned object will be wrapped in an Optional. So there will never be null passed to function f.
        Type Parameters:
        I - type of input object to be mapped to type O
        O - type of output of the mapping
        Parameters:
        f - function that's output will be wrapped into an optional. If the input value is null, the function will not be called.
        Returns:
        Function, either returning an Optional containing the output of function f, or an empty Optional if the input is null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if f is null.

      • test

        public static <T> AdvPredicate<T> test(Predicate<T> p)
        Takes a Predicate and returns an AdvPredicate performing the same test. This can be used to make function references (to static or member methods) explicitly available as predicates, which can be handy if a lambda expression would be ambiguous (e.g. other functional interfaces can be expected in a certain context). It also allows easy composition of functions using the methods on Predicate, like Predicate.and(java.util.function.Predicate) or Predicate.or(java.util.function.Predicate). Example: 
         
   test(String::isEmpty).not()
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of object to be checked by predicate p
        Parameters:
        p - predicate that should be made available as an AdvPredicate
        Returns:
        AdvPredicate representation of predicate p
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if p is null.

        Function tries to cast the given object to the specified class. If the object is instance of the given class the method will return an Optional containing the casted object. If the object is not instance of the specified class, the result will be an empty Optional.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type the input object is casted to, if it is instance of this type
        Parameters:
        o - object to be casted
        clazz - class to cast parameter o to.
        Returns:
        if o is instance of clazz, an Optional containing o casted to clazz. Otherwise an empty Optional.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if clazz is null.

      • filter

        public static <I> OptionalMapper<I,I> filter(Predicate<I> test)
                                      throws NullPointerException
        Creates a function that checks if the given predicate test returns true for input objects passed to that function. Depending on the outcome, the function will either return an empty Optional (if the predicate returns false) or an Optional holding the input object (if the predicate returns true).
        Type Parameters:
        I - type of element to be tested by test
        Parameters:
        test - predicate to check if input objects should be wrapped in an optional. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        function mapping from I to Optional<I>, based on predicate test.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if test is null.

      • filterNullAware

        public static <I> OptionalMapper<I,I> filterNullAware(Predicate<I> test)
                                               throws NullPointerException
        Creates a function that will return the input wrapped in an optional if it is not null and predicate test returns true for this input. Otherwise it will return an empty optional. If the given predicate throws an exception the exception will be thrown to the caller of the returned filter function.
        Type Parameters:
        I - type of input object to returned function
        Parameters:
        test - predicate checking if the input will be returned in an optional, or if an empty optional will be returned. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        function filtering the input out if it is null or does not match predicate test.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if test is null.

        Throws:

      • typed

        public static <I,O> TypeCheck<I,O> typed(Class<O> clazz)
                                  throws NullPointerException
        This predicate checks if an object is exactly of the given type. This is not an instanceof check, since this would also return true if the object was of a subtype of the class in question.
        Type Parameters:
        I - type of input element checked to be of type T
        O - type the input element is checked to be of
        Parameters:
        clazz - Class the predicate checks input objects are type of.
        Returns:
        Predicate testing if an object is exactly of the given type.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if clazz is null.

      • instanceOf

        public static <I,O> TypeCheck<I,O> instanceOf(Class<O> clazz)
                                       throws NullPointerException
        The returned predicate checks if an input object is instance of the given class. This predicate allows follow up checks on the input object, that will automatically be cased to the checked type.
        Type Parameters:
        I - type of input element to be checked to be instance of T
        O - type the input is checked to be instance of.
        Parameters:
        clazz - type input objects are checked to be instance of
        Returns:
        predicate checking input objects if they are instance of class clazz.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if clazz is null.

      • eq

        public static <T> AdvPredicate<T> eq(T t)
        Returns predicate checking if input objects are equal to the given object t. Equality check is performed using Objects.equals(Object, Object).
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type of element to be checked for equality
        Parameters:
        t - object to check for equality
        Returns:
        predicate, checking input objects for equality to t.

      • oneOf

        public static <T> AdvPredicate<T> oneOf(T t,
                                        T... more)
                                 throws NullPointerException
        Returns predicate that returns true if the input object is one of the given objects t or more. The function will use referential equality to check if the input is one of the give objects. Be aware that changes to the given elements more will have no effect on the returned predicate.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of elements to be checked
        Parameters:
        t - one element predicate will check if input is equal to it
        more - further elements the predicate will check if element is one of them.
        Returns:
        predicate checking if the input object is either t or one of more.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - will be thrown if more is null.

      • refEq

        public static <T> AdvPredicate<T> refEq(Object o)
        Creates predicate checking for referential equality. The predicate will use the == operator and does not call any equals method.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of element checked for referential equality with parameter o.
        Parameters:
        o - to be checked for referential equality.
        Returns:
        predicate checking an input for referential equality with parameter o.
